			<p><em>(*) Laser therapy is evaluated by medical experts in Vietnam as well as in the world as one of the most effective Physiotherapy (VLTL) methods today.</em></p>
<p><em>With a team of highly skilled therapists and a system of modern and safe equipment, customers can rest assured when experiencing laser therapy at Zara therapy clinic.</em></p>
<p><span id="more-31935"></span></p>
<h4><strong>WHAT IS LASER THERAPY?</strong></h4>
<p>Laser is an acronym for Light Amplification by Stimulated Emission of Radiation.</p>
<p> Laser therapy is a treatment that uses focused light to precisely target the damaged area without harming the surrounding areas.</p>
<p>The laser will go deep into the damaged cells in the treatment of joint pain, spinal pain, muscle pain, ligament damage, neuralgia, ... to stimulate the motor points in neuromuscular recovery, Improves the resilience of damaged cells.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-31936" src="{{asset('baiviet/laser.jpg')}}"></p>
<h4><strong>EFFECTS OF LASER THERAPY</strong></h4>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Pain relief</li>
<li>Anti-inflammatory</li> 
<li>Anti-edema</li>
<li>Biological stimulation (Impact on living characteristics such as: protein biosynthesis, biomass accumulation process, cellular respiration process.)</li>
<li>Stimulate tissue regeneration, heal wounds, ulcers</li>
<li>Thermal effect: vasodilation, muscle relaxation</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-31704" src="{{asset('baiviet/dieu-tri-laser-1-1.png')}}"></p>
<h4><strong>UNDER WHAT CIRCUMSTANCES IS LASER THERAPY USED?</strong></h4>
<p>Laser therapy is indicated in cases such as:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Muscle injuries (muscle tension, muscle spasms, muscle lacerations)</li>
<li>Ligament damage</li>
<li>Arthritis, osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis</li>
<li>Tendinitis (heel tendon – Achilles, Tenis Elbow, rotating spire tendon, carpal tunnel syndrome, tendon around the shoulder joint, patellar tendon,...)</li>
<li>Herniated disc</li>
<li>Neck - shoulder - nape pain, low back pain</li>
<li>Sciatica</li>
</ul>
<p>&#8212;&#8211;</p>
<p>Coming to Zara therapy clinic, customers will experience the most modern and advanced VLTL machines. With each different injury case, Zara therapy clinic Doctors and Specialists will advise and select the most necessary and suitable machines, bringing the highest efficiency to the course of treatment and injury recovery.</p>
<p>With our professionalism, dedication and prestige, we are confident that we can bring satisfaction to each customer when experiencing the service at Zara therapy clinic
.</p>
<p><strong><em>For advice and to schedule an appointment, please contact hotline  0379348103.</em></strong></p>
